Description: Model Context Protocol SDK (Avalan PPA pin)
 The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a JSON-RPC dialect that lets
 LLM-driven clients enumerate and invoke tools, prompts, and resources
 exposed by a server. The `mcp` Python SDK provides typed client /
 server primitives and a stdio transport. Avalan ships it in its
 `server` extras at `>= 1.12.3, < 2.0.0`; nothing in Debian carries
 it, so the rebuild pins 1.27.1.
 .
 Two upstream runtime dependencies (`sse-starlette`, `pydantic-settings`)
 and the `[crypto]` extra of `pyjwt` are intentionally not declared as
 Depends. They are only reached from FastMCP's HTTP/SSE transports and
 the OAuth authentication handlers, which Noble's archive does not
 carry. Avalan exercises only the JSON-RPC types and the stdio
 transport, both of which work without those modules. Callers that pull
 `mcp.server.fastmcp` or `mcp.server.sse` get a clear ImportError
 telling them which package is missing.
